title: St. Francis volleyball sweeps through Leland quad
text:
St. Francis volleyball sweeps through Leland quad Posted: Updated: 
LELAND - A volleyball quad at Leland featured a pair of state-ranked teams but only one swept the day. Fifth-ranked St. Francis swept McBain NMC, Traverse City Christian and the third-ranked Comets Thursday night. 
Leland swept the Sabres and Comets to finish the night with a pair of wins to their one loss. 
T.C. Christian defeated McBain NMC 2-1 to give the Sabres their lone victory Thursday night.
